The time has come to tear down our bedroom. The last room in the house where nothing has been done, just a little decoration.
Remove the horrible electric heater and fireplace. Encase the chimney, replace the damaged plaster, and sand. Build a custom closet.
One always starts with a quick sketch in pencil...
The stain-removing step is complete.
I found several dead birds at the back of the chimney; all dried up :(.
Ready for the plasterer next week
Pleased with the small niche on the side.
Insert the new wardrobe here (it's not like we've already started drawing it 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the radiator!
And they even thought about adding a charming little air vent to prevent the chimney from getting damp.
The chimney sweep took care of installing the cap and the spark arrestor. It should be a bit safer for the crows nesting up there 🪺
The plasterer is done. The floor is being installed tomorrow!
The cork underlayer is laid, I improvised a wood shavings extractor with a roll of toilet paper as an attachment for the vacuum cleaner 😂
Part of the planks have been sorted and are ready to be installed. We're just taking a tea break.
Well, progress has been slow today because of very delicate cuts around the door frames to achieve a smooth transition into the hallway (which is also being installed). @user45@twitter.com cursed me.
Done, but on our knees! Cherry on top: the impossible instructions for assembling the new bed. We'll sleep well tonight!
Left to do are the floor of the hallway and all the skirtings. The decorator is coming in a month, so in the meantime, at home, it's the charm of raw plaster.
A little evening DIY session to remove the lower sections of the door posts with a miter saw or a hand saw at the spot where you want the floor to fit perfectly.
The cork underlayer of the corridor is also laid.
We finished the floor of the hallway yesterday! Then departure at 5 a.m. this morning to pick up Thing 1 at Heathrow, after that a nap and the final stretch for the hallway; the skirting boards are installed. We'll take care of the insulation once the adhesive has dried.
